GEN_name: Tullio de Piscopo and Tony Esposito
GEN_description: Their story is incredible: it has revolutionised the Italian music by building new bridges between tradition, funk, jazz, soul, pop.Tullio De Piscopo and Tony Esposito, each in their own way, have always known and wanted to find the right balance between show and deep technical knowledge, between the desire to communicate and the ability to always respect rules, roots, intensity.In the 70's they played alongside Pino Daniele in the legendary Napoli Centrale, and in the following decades as soloists and band leaders.

As every winter, the music of Arte Sella Fucina Bianca celebrates the transition to a new year of Arte Sella, with the participation of interpreters of international renown, invited by the artistic director Mario Brunello.(Translation by Denis Cova, Sophie M. Scholl Language High School, Trento - “School and Work Project”)
